"## üìë Overview\n",
"Prompt engineering is the practice of developing and optimizing prompts to efficiently use language models for a variety of applications.\n",
"\n",
"## ‚öôÔ∏è Part 1: LLM Settings\n",
"| Parameter | Impact | Usage |\n",
"| :--- | :--- | :--- |\n",
"| Temperature | Controls randomness | 0.2 (Predictable/Fact-based) to 0.8 (Creative/Varied) |\n",
"| Top P | Nucleus Sampling | Determines the range of possible next words |\n",
"| Max Length | Output Limit | Prevents excessively long or irrelevant outputs |\n",
"| Penalties | Repetition Control | Frequency and Presence penalties to vary vocabulary |"
]
},
{
"cell_type": "code",
"execution_count": null,
"metadata": {},
"outputs": [],
"source": [
"# Setup libraries\n",
"!pip install openai\n",
"from openai import OpenAI\n",
"\n",
"client = OpenAI(api_key="") # Add your API key here\n",
"\n",
"def get_completion(prompt, temp=0.7):\n",
"    response = client.chat.completions.create(\n",
"        model="gpt-4o-mini",\n",
"        messages=[{"role": "user", "content": prompt}],\n",
"        temperature=temp\n",
"    )\n",
"    return response.choices[0].message.content"
]
},
{
"cell_type": "markdown",
"metadata": {},
"source": [
"## üß† Part 2: Advanced Techniques\n",
"\n",
"### 1. Chain-of-Thought (CoT)\n",
"Slide Example: A juggler can juggle 16 balls. Half of the balls are golf balls, and half of the golf balls are blue. How many blue golf balls are there?"
]
},
{
"cell_type": "code",
"execution_count": null,
"metadata": {},
"outputs": [],
"source": [
"prompt = "A juggler can juggle 16 balls. Half are golf balls, and half of the golf balls are blue. How many blue golf balls are there? Let's think step by step."\n",
"print(get_completion(prompt))"
]
},
{
"cell_type": "markdown",
"metadata": {},
"source": [
"### 2. Program-Aided Language (PAL)\n",
"Slide Example: The bakers baked 200 loaves. Sold 93 in the morning and 39 in the afternoon. 6 were returned. How many left?"
]
},
{
"cell_type": "code",
"execution_count": null,
"metadata": {},
"outputs": [],
"source": [
"pal_prompt = "Q: Bakers baked 200 loaves. Sold 93 in AM, 39 in PM. 6 returned. How many left? A: Write a Python snippet to solve this."\n",
"print(get_completion(pal_prompt))"
]
},
{
"cell_type": "markdown",
"metadata": {},
"source": [
"### 3. ReAct (Reason + Act)\n",
"Slide Example: Search for Apple Remote's original program and other devices that control it."
]
},
{
"cell_type": "code",
"execution_count": null,
"metadata": {},
"outputs": [],
"source": [
"react_prompt = """\n",
"Thought 1: I need to search Apple Remote and find the program it was originally designed to interact with.\n",
"Action 1: Search [Apple Remote]\n",
"Observation 1: Originally designed to control the Front Row media center program.\n",
"Thought 2: Now I need to find what other device can control Front Row.\n",
""""\n",
"print(get_completion(react_prompt))"
]
}
